<h1>My Eye Tracker Session — Decision Guide</h1>
<p class="subtitle">Infant Head-Mounted Eye Tracker · Data Collection Scenario</p>

<div class="flowchart">

  <!-- START -->
  <div class="node node-start">
    <div class="node-label">Situation</div>
    <div class="node-text">The eye tracker is not recording properly during my infant session</div>
    <div class="node-sub">The infant is fussy and upset. I need to make a decision.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>

  <!-- ASSESS -->
  <div class="node node-assess">
    <div class="node-label">Step 1 · Assess the Situation</div>
    <div class="node-text">I evaluate the infant's distress level and data quality in real time</div>
    <div class="node-sub">How fussy is the infant? Am I capturing any usable data? How far into the session am I?</div>
  </div>

  <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>

  <!-- DECISION -->
  <div class="node node-decision">
    <div class="node-label">Step 2 · Key Decision</div>
    <div class="node-text">Should I leave the device on or remove it?</div>
  </div>

  <!-- BRANCH -->
  <div class="branch-wrapper">
    <div class="branch-container">

      <!-- KEEP ON -->
      <div class="branch branch-keep">
        <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>
        <div class="branch-header">Option A · Leave it on</div>
        <div class="node node-action-keep">
          <div class="node-label">Tradeoff</div>
          <div class="node-text">Higher likelihood of capturing some data, even if quality is reduced</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-cons-title">Pros</div>
          <div class="pro-item">Greater chance of obtaining data</div>
          <div class="pro-item">Avoids disrupting the session</div>
          <div class="pros-cons-title" style="margin-top:8px">Cons</div>
          <div class="con-item">Data quality is likely poor</div>
          <div class="con-item">Infant remains uncomfortable</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- REMOVE -->
      <div class="branch branch-remove">
        <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>
        <div class="branch-header">Option B · Remove it</div>
        <div class="node node-action-remove">
          <div class="node-label">Tradeoff</div>
          <div class="node-text">Opportunity to recalibrate for better results and comfort the infant</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-cons-title">Pros</div>
          <div class="pro-item">I can recalibrate for better data</div>
          <div class="pro-item">May reduce infant's fussiness</div>
          <div class="pros-cons-title" style="margin-top:8px">Cons</div>
          <div class="con-item">Infant may refuse to wear it again</div>
          <div class="con-item">Could upset the infant further</div>
          <div class="con-item">May appear unprofessional to caregivers</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- MERGE -->
    <div class="merge-line">
      <div class="merge-line-left"></div>
      <div class="merge-down"><div class="merge-dot"></div></div>
      <div class="merge-line-right"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- COMMUNICATE WITH CAREGIVER -->
  <div class="node node-comm">
    <div class="node-label">Step 3 · Communicate with Caregiver</div>
    <div class="node-text">I am transparent with the infant's caregiver</div>
    <div class="node-sub">I clearly explain that the device is not operating properly and that another session may be needed. I keep my tone calm and reassuring.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>

  <!-- COMMUNICATE WITH TEAM -->
  <div class="node node-comm expandable" onclick="toggleExpand(this)">
    <div class="node-label">Step 4 · Communicate with My Team <span class="expand-icon">▶</span></div>
    <div class="node-text">I loop in my lab assistant, PI, or relevant team members</div>
    <div class="toggle-hint">Click to see how ▶</div>
    <div class="expandable-content">
      <div class="node-sub">
        <strong>In the moment:</strong> I use Slack, Teams, or whichever channel makes sense to briefly flag what happened and the decision I made.<br><br>
        <strong>Back in the lab:</strong> I walk through my thought process in person, explain the tradeoffs I weighed, and ask for feedback. This shows initiative and professional self-reflection.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="connector"><div class="connector-line"></div><div class="connector-arrow"></div></div>

  <!-- END -->
  <div class="node node-end">
    <div class="node-label">Outcome</div>
    <div class="node-text">I document the session, note the data quality issue, and schedule a follow-up if needed</div>
    <div class="node-sub">I reflect on the decision and use team feedback to inform my future sessions.</div>
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  function toggleExpand(el) {
    el.classList.toggle('expanded');
    const content = el.querySelector('.expandable-content');
    content.classList.toggle('open');
    const hint = el.querySelector('.toggle-hint');
    if (content.classList.contains('open')) {
      hint.textContent = 'Click to collapse ▲';
    } else {
      hint.textContent = 'Click to see how ▶';
    }
  }
</script>

